race.comment: SABINO (7) led them up over 1760m at Kalgoorlie and failed to run out the extra journey following a strong performance over 1300m prior. Cheung's 2kg claim comes in handy and the drop back to this distance is a very good move. Can end his winning drought. FORTUNE'S LUCK (1) will find this much easier than what she's been racing in, going around as a $14 chance in town last start. She's right back to country level today first-up for the new stable and if she can hold her recent form, she'll take beating. DEAL OBTAINED (4) is better than he's produced recently, finishing well back at My Magnet last time out. His run three back at Junction was very good however and the 21 days between runs may spark him back to that form. Leading chance. RULING DAME (6) may need some luck but is not out of this if the breaks come. SHASFA (9) is worth including.
